headline: AI Stocks Wobble As Spending Balloons. Another DeepSeek Dip, or a Dark Fiber Moment?
summary: If data-center investments were to decline suddenly by 20%, S&P 500 earnings estimates would take only a 3% to 4% hit, Barclays reckons.

headline: Micron's DRAM Revenues Hit $28.6B: Can the Momentum Continue?
summary: MU's DRAM sales surge 62% to $28.6B in fiscal 2025, fueled by HBM demand for AI servers and tight supply boosting margins.
